// Cheet Sheet for Working with GIT

I. High Level Steps in managing the code changes

0. Clone repository - git clone <Repo URL>
1. Pull changes - git pull
2. Make changes - Add, remove, modify files
3. Staging changes - git add file/folder
4. Commit changes - git commit -m "Commit message"
5. Push your files - git push origin branchName

II. Steps to Push a Local Repository into Git Hub

1. Initialise Local Repository
    git init

2. Configure Remote Repository
    git config --global user.email "f.vinodhfranklin@gmail.com"
    git config --global user.name "fvinodh1978"  

3. Configure Remote repository
   git remote add origin https://github.com/fvinodh1978/CircleCi-Demo.git

4. To verify that you set the remote URL correctly, run the following command.
    git remote -v

5. Create a Branch in Remote Repository
   git checkout -b ＜new-branch＞

6. Add files to Git Staging
   git add .

7. Remove Files from Git Staging Area
   git reset

8. Commit the code into Git
   git commit -m "Initial Commit"
    
9. push the files to specific remote git Branch
   git push -u origin master
